KANO – National Leader of the New Nigeria People’s Party, Senator Rabiu Musa Kwankwaso on Wednesday said he was saddened by the passing of Kano Influential politician, Alhaji Musa Gwadabe. Malam Musa Gwadabe 87, who was a minister of Labour, and Productivity was reported dead by his family on Tuesday night. The Presidential candidate of the NNPP in a statement that was made available to INDEPENDENT on Wednesday said “I am deeply saddened by the passing of Alhaji Musa Gwadabe. “ The strong man of Kano politics explained in the statement that “The Elder Statesman and former Minister was an upright politician who stood for his ideals.” Kwankwaso therefore said “I extend my condolences to his family, and the good people of Kano State.” He, therefore, prayed unto “Almighty Allah grant him Jannatul Firdaus, and protect his legacy.”